paragraph.def:
“consular
                        post” means any consulate-general, consulate, vice-consulate, or
                    consular agency;

“head of
                        consular post” means the person charged with the duty of acting in
                    that capacity;

“consular
                        officer” means any person, including the head of a consular post,
                    entrusted in that capacity with the exercise of consular functions;

“member of the administrative and technical staff of the
                        consular post” means any person who performs administrative or
                    technical services at a consular post;

“member
                        of the service staff” means any person employed in the domestic
                    service of a consular post;

“members
                        of a consular post” means consular officers, administrative and
                    technical staff and service staff of a consular post;

“family
                        members” means the spouse, children and parents who are dependent on
                    a member of a consular post and forming part of the same household;

“national of the sending State” means any natural person having the
                    nationality of the sending State, and, when applicable, also any juridical
                    person of the sending State;

paragraph.content:
arising out of a contract concluded by a member of the consular post in
                    which he did not contract expressly or impliedly as an agent of the sending
                    State;

concerning private immovable property in the receiving State, unless a
                    member of the consular post is holding it in the capacity of representative of
                    the sending State and for the purposes of the consular post;

consular premises and residences of the members of a consular post acquired
                    in the name of the sending State or its representative and transactions or
                    instruments related thereto;
